A platform team is migrating a self-hosted Temporal cluster to Temporal Cloud. They have configured mTLS with per-worker client certificates (rotated every 30 days via cert-manager) and a custom Data Converter with a remote Payload Codec that calls an internal KMS for envelope encryption. During the migration cutover, some workflows that were started on the self-hosted cluster are being continued via Continue-As-New on the new Temporal Cloud namespace. Engineers observe that Query handlers on these continued workflows return correctly decrypted data when called from internal tooling, but the payloads stored in Temporal Cloud's visibility store appear as opaque encrypted blobs rather than decoded values — even though custom search attributes are being set correctly. Which interaction between these features explains this behavior, and what is the correct remediation?

```python
@workflow.defn
class MigratedWorkflow:
    def __init__(self):
        self._status = ""

    @workflow.run
    async def run(self) -> None:
        self._status = await workflow.execute_activity(
            fetch_status, schedule_to_close_timeout=timedelta(seconds=30)
        )
        workflow.upsert_search_attributes(
            {"CustomStatus": [self._status]}
        )
        workflow.continue_as_new()

    @workflow.query
    def current_status(self) -> str:
        return self._status
```
